	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I use ASM6 because there is no bureaucracy at all, as there isn't absolutely nothing to set up. The ROM can be built from a single file (good for starting out, but definitely not good for large projects) if you want to, and it's possible to get a iNES file ready for emulators in one go. I like it because it's so simple, but also so versatile.

		

		</td>
